                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-325-victim2676 t18320906-325-viclabel1841"></join>. I lost a cloak at <placeName id="t18320906-325-crimeloc1842">Southgate fair</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-325-crimeloc1842" type="placeName" value="Southgate fair"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-325-crimeloc1842" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-325-off1838 t18320906-325-crimeloc1842"></join>, on the 1st of September, about eleven o'clock at night - I had left it in my booth; I sell beer -I found the prisoner about five yards from the booth with it, under his arm; I had received information, went out, and Craskin pointed him out to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-325-person2678">
                  THOMAS 
                  CRASKIN
               <interp inst="t18320906-325-person2678" type="surname" value="CRASKIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-325-person2678" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-325-person2678" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was employed by Beard at Southgate fair, and saw the prisoner outside the booth looking through a hole in the canvas; his mate, who was with him, asked what I wanted, and while I was looking at the prisoner his mate knocked me down with a great stick - they were in company; I got up in a minute or two, and called for assistance; my master came out - I had seen the prisoner cut the booth, and take the coat out - I pointed him out to master, who came, and took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-325-person2679">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CRANE
               <interp inst="t18320906-325-person2679" type="surname" value="CRANE"></interp>
